tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE EnergyData (
    date DATE,
    time TIME,
    location VARCHAR(255),
    energy_consumption FLOAT,
    energy_generation FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE energy_consumption (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    time TIME,
    location VARCHAR,
    consumption DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE energy_generation (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    time TIME,
    location VARCHAR,
    generation DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE energy_trends (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    consumption DECIMAL,
    generation DECIMAL,
    trend VARCHAR
)

CREATE TABLE energy_consumption (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  location VARCHAR(100),
  consumption_kwh FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE energy_generation (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  location VARCHAR(100),
  generation_kwh FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE energy_sources (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  source_name VARCHAR(100),
  type VARCHAR(50),
  capacity_kwh FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE energy_trends (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  trend_type VARCHAR(50),
  value FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE energy_consumption (
    consumption_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    location VARCHAR(50),
    consumption_date TIMESTAMP,
    energy_consumed FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE energy_generation (
    generation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    location VARCHAR(50),
    generation_date TIMESTAMP,
    energy_generated FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE solar_panels (
    panel_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    location VARCHAR(50),
    efficiency FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE weather_data (
    weather_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    location VARCHAR(50),
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE energy_analysis (
    analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    time_period VARCHAR(50),
    trends TEXT,
    optimized_strategy TEXT
)
